"Wireless network is one of the n iche areas and has been a growing interest owing to their ability to control the physical environment even from remote locations. Intelligent routing, bandwidth allocation and power control techniques are the known crit ical factors for this network communication. It is customary to find a feasible path between the communicat ion end point which is a challenging task in this type of network. The present study proposes an Ant Mobility Model (AMM), an on-demand, multi-path routing algorithm that exercises power control and coordinate the nodes to communicate with one another in wireless network. The main goal of this protocol is to reduce the overhead, congestion, and stagnation, while increasing the throughput of the network. It can be realized from the simulation results that AMM proves to be a promising solution for the mobility pattern in wireless networks like MANETs."
